parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
Using a spare tire with a different size than the other tires can cause uneven tire wear, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: but potential risks include loss of control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power sliding door can cause unexpected opening or closure, leading to injuries or accidents, especially when occupants are entering or exiting the vehicle.
symptoms: The power sliding door opens or closes unexpectedly
the door opens too far or gets stuck
the door does not respond to commands.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake booster can cause the vehicle to become difficult to stop, requiring excessive pressure on the brake pedal, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the brake pedal requires extreme pressure to stop the vehicle
the brakes work normally after removing the ABS fuse.
